# {{projectName}}

NestJS + Nuxt 4 monorepo scaffolded with [nuxest](https://github.com/your-org/nuxest).

## Quick start (Docker — recommended)

Runs the app and all selected services (database, Redis, etc.) in containers:

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

Open **http://localhost:{{nestPort}}**

Use `pnpm docker:down` to stop containers.

The `app` container runs as your host user (UID/GID baked in at scaffold time) so `node_modules` is not owned by root. If you have root-owned volumes from an earlier run, reset with `docker compose down -v`.

## Quick start (local app)

Run the app on your host and use Docker only for infrastructure:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
{{#if hasInfraServices}}docker compose up -d {{infraServices}}
{{/if}}pnpm dev
```

`.env.example` uses `localhost` URLs for this workflow. The `app` service in `docker-compose.yml` overrides them with in-network hostnames.

{{#if admin}}
Admin panel: **http://localhost:{{nestPort}}/admin**
{{/if}}

## Scripts

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `pnpm dev` | Nest on `:{{nestPort}}` + Nuxt on `:{{nuxtDevPort}}` (on host) |
| `pnpm build` | Production build |
| `pnpm start:prod` | Run production server |
| `pnpm test` | API tests |
| `pnpm docker:up` | Start full dev stack in background |
| `pnpm docker:dev` | Start full dev stack (foreground, with logs) |
| `pnpm docker:down` | Stop containers |

## Structure

```
apps/api          NestJS backend (HTTP entry, /api/*)
apps/web          Nuxt 4 frontend ({{nuxtMode}})
packages/shared   Shared TypeScript types
```

